     <section id="specInfo" class="block">
      <h2 class="subtitle is-inline is-bold">Special Information: </h2>This course is considered refresher certification training for Navy and Marine Corps military, civilian, and contractor personnel who conduct the inspection of railcars used to transport A&E and hazardous material shipments as prescribed by DoDI 5160.68, and other personnel who must fulfill certification requirements prescribed by NAVSEA OP 5, Volume 1, and NAVSEA SW023-AK-SAF-010. Personnel seeking initial certification training must successfully complete the instructor-led version of the course, Course No. 4E-F40/645-F24 (MC), NAVAL MOTOR VEH & RAILCAR INSPECTION (CERT). This course is a web-based (online) course. Students must have web access, a CAC card, and an Navy E-Learning (NEL) account. Students must register through NEL for course credit. A high-speed Internet connection is recommended to complete the course.
